   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SIX IN THE CONSUMMATION OF</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE NEW JERUSALEM Scripture Reading: 2 Pet 3:10-12; Rev 21:1; 22:1; 21:6; 22:17b; John 4:14; 7:37-39; Rev 22:2, 14; 2:7; 21:3, 22, 11 OUTLINE The New Jerusalem being the consummation of all the works of God's new creation out of His old creation in all the dispensations through the ages, including: The ages in the Old Testament: The age before the law, from Adam to Moses.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The age of the law, from Moses to Christ's first coming.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The ages in the New Testament: The age of grace, from Christ's first coming to His second coming.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The age of the kingdom, from Christ's second coming to the end of the old creation 2 Pet 3:10-12; Rev 21:1 .</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The New Jerusalem being the aggregate of God's organic union and mingling with His redeemed, regenerated, transformed, and glorified people: The constitution of God as life in the redeemed humanity.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The organic building of divinity with humanity.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>With the processed Triune God to be the flowing river of water of life as the very center and the very source of supply of the holy city Rev 22:1: To quench organically the thirst of God's people mingled and built together with God for eternity Rev 21:6; 22:17b; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>John 4:14; 7:37-39.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>To satisfy organically the entire city with Christ as the tree of life growing in the river of water of life for eternity Rev 22:2, 14; 2:7.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The New Jerusalem being God's ultimate organism: For the redeeming God to dwell organically in His redeemed people as His tabernacle for eternity Rev 21:3.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>For God's redeemed people to dwell organically in their redeeming God as their temple for eternity Rev 21:22.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>As the processed Triune God's eternal manifestation and expression: With the processed Triune God as the glory of its content Rev 21:11a.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>With the conformed people as the shining light of its appearance Rev 21:11b.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The ultimate issue of the organic union in God's relationship with man in His life which is unsearchably rich in eternity.</S>
   </TEXT>
